│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure inside                      │
│ CallBase::paramHasNonNullAttr, which requires the queried argument to be │
│ a pointer-typed operand. In the provided IR, a call is made with a <2 x  │
│ ptr> argument (vector of pointers). SimplifyCFG's                        │
│ passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined calls paramHasNonNullAttr on the argument  │
│ operand without ensuring it is a pointer type, thus violating the        │
│ precondition when the operand is a vector of pointers.                   │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                  │
│ The stack trace shows the failure at CallBase::paramHasNonNullAttr,      │
│ invoked from passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined (SimplifyCFG.cpp:8226/8227).  │
│ The reproducer demonstrates a vector GEP producing a <2 x ptr> that is   │
│ passed to a function. SimplifyCFG tries to reason about undefined        │
│ behavior when passing null to a nonnull+noundef argument. However, the   │
│ code assumes pointer type and doesn't guard for vector types, leading to │
│ the assertion.                                                           │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ Within passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined, the code does:                     │
│   if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C) && CB->paramHasNonNullAttr(ArgIdx,     │
│ false))                                                                  │
│ This assumes the argument is a pointer operand. When the operand is a    │
│ vector of pointers, getArgOperand(ArgNo)->getType()->isPointerTy() is    │
│ false, triggering the assert in paramHasNonNullAttr. The logic should    │
│ only apply this pointer-specific check when the argument operand is      │
│ actually a pointer. Currently there is no type guard.                    │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ Add a type check before calling paramHasNonNullAttr to ensure the        │
│ argument operand is pointer-typed. If it is not a pointer (e.g., vector  │
│ of pointers), skip the pointer-specific nonnull handling path.           │
│ Specifically, change:                                                    │
│   if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C) &&                                     │
│       CB->paramHasNonNullAttr(ArgIdx, /*AllowUndefOrPoison=*/false))     │
│     return !PtrValueMayBeModified;                                       │
│ into:                                                                    │
│   if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C)) {                                     │
│     Type *ArgTy = CB->getArgOperand(ArgIdx)->getType();                  │
│     if (ArgTy->isPointerTy() &&                                          │
│         CB->paramHasNonNullAttr(ArgIdx, /*AllowUndefOrPoison=*/false))   │
│       return !PtrValueMayBeModified;                                     │
│   }                                                                      │
│ This preserves existing semantics for pointer-typed arguments and avoids │
│ calling paramHasNonNullAttr for non-pointer types, preventing the        │
│ assert.                                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ Edit point:                                                              │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp                        │
│ - Lines: 8223-8229                                                       │
│ - Change as described above.                                             │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The fix adds a type guard around the use of paramHasNonNullAttr,         │
│ ensuring it is only called for pointer-typed arguments. This resolves    │
│ the crash when encountering vector-of-pointers arguments, while          │
│ maintaining the intended UB reasoning for pointer arguments. The         │
│ expected effect is that simplifycfg no longer aborts on the provided     │
│ reproducer and continues analysis safely.                                │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
